# AaaS Product Template — Cursor Rules

## Architecture
- Maximum 600 lines per file. Split by responsibility if approaching limit.
- One file = one purpose. No monolithic modules.
- Follow the modular structure defined in CLAUDE.md.

## JavaScript
- ES modules with explicit imports/exports
- No global state mutations — use the module pattern
- Event delegation over individual listeners
- Async/await for all API calls
- Descriptive function names: `loadDashboardStats()` not `load()`
- Max 30 lines per function

## CSS
- Use CSS custom properties from theme.css (never hardcode colors)
- BEM-like naming: `.section-card`, `.section-card-header`
- Mobile-first responsive design
- No `!important` unless overriding third-party styles

## Python
- Type hints on all function signatures
- Dataclasses over plain dicts for structured data
- Context managers for database sessions (`with session_scope()`)
- FastAPI dependency injection for auth/config
- No bare `except:` — always specify exception type

## Security
- Validate user input at API boundaries
- Parameterized queries only (SQLAlchemy ORM)
- Sanitize HTML output (XSS prevention)
- Never expose secrets client-side
- API keys: prefix display only, hash storage

## Testing
- Run `pytest tests/ -v` before commits
- Test behavior, not implementation details
- New features require tests; bug fixes require regression tests

## Protected Files
These files have readonly protection — do not modify without explicit unlock:
- `product_app/security.py` — Authentication system
- `product_app/models.py` — Database schema
- `product_app/stripe_billing.py` — Billing integration
- `product_app/database.py` — Database connection

## Agent Development
- Subclass `ResearchStyleBase` in `product_app/research/`
- Implement: `build_pipeline()`, `get_stages()`, `get_section_titles()`
- End file with `STYLE = MyStyle()` for auto-discovery
- Use `SequentialAgent` or `ParallelAgent` from ADK for pipelines

## Vibe Coding Tips
- Start with the Getting Started guide in the workspace
- Focus on frontend (landing, chat UI, components) — agents are backend
- Each section is its own JS module — edit one at a time
- Check How It Works for agent pipeline diagrams
- Use placeholder components as starting points
